{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1387,"text":"Everything is covered in invisible ecosystems"},{"time":5106,"text":"made of tiny lifeforms: bacteria, viruses and fungi."},{"time":9594,"text":"Our desks, our computers, our pencils, our buildings"},{"time":13698,"text":"all harbor resident microbial landscapes."},{"time":17154,"text":"As we design these things, we could be thinking"},{"time":19914,"text":"about designing these invisible worlds,"},{"time":22728,"text":"and also thinking about how they interact"},{"time":24971,"text":"with our personal ecosystems."}]},{"cues":[{"time":27727,"text":"Our bodies are home to trillions of microbes,"},{"time":31370,"text":"and these creatures define who we are."},{"time":33730,"text":"The microbes in your gut can influence your weight and your moods."},{"time":37608,"text":"The microbes on your skin can help boost your immune system."},{"time":41066,"text":"The microbes in your mouth can freshen your breath,"},{"time":44075,"text":"or not,"},{"time":45547,"text":"and the key thing is that our personal ecosystems"},{"time":48526,"text":"interact with ecosystems on everything we touch."},{"time":51594,"text":"So, for example, when you touch a pencil,"},{"time":53186,"text":"microbial exchange happens."}]},{"cues":[{"time":56018,"text":"If we can design the invisible ecosystems in our surroundings,"},{"time":60914,"text":"this opens a path to influencing"},{"time":63537,"text":"our health in unprecedented ways."}]},{"cues":[{"time":66928,"text":"I get asked all of the time from people,"},{"time":69392,"text":"\"Is it possible to really design microbial ecosystems?\""},{"time":73462,"text":"And I believe the answer is yes."},{"time":76010,"text":"I think we're doing it right now,"},{"time":77935,"text":"but we're doing it unconsciously."},{"time":81043,"text":"I'm going to share data with you"},{"time":83008,"text":"from one aspect of my research focused on architecture"},{"time":86736,"text":"that demonstrates how, through both conscious"},{"time":89862,"text":"and unconscious design,"},{"time":92072,"text":"we're impacting these invisible worlds."}]},{"cues":[{"time":95081,"text":"This is the Lillis Business Complex at the University of Oregon,"},{"time":99310,"text":"and I worked with a team of architects and biologists"},{"time":101994,"text":"to sample over 300 rooms in this building."},{"time":106168,"text":"We wanted to get something like a fossil record of the building,"},{"time":110178,"text":"and to do this, we sampled dust."},{"time":113488,"text":"From the dust, we pulled out bacterial cells,"},{"time":117396,"text":"broke them open, and compared their gene sequences."},{"time":120800,"text":"This means that people in my group"},{"time":122527,"text":"were doing a lot of vacuuming during this project."},{"time":125840,"text":"This is a picture of Tim, who,"},{"time":128360,"text":"right when I snapped this picture, reminded me,"},{"time":130814,"text":"he said, \"Jessica, the last lab group I worked in"},{"time":133384,"text":"I was doing fieldwork in the Costa Rican rainforest,"},{"time":136355,"text":"and things have changed dramatically for me.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":140112,"text":"So I'm going to show you now first what we found in the offices,"},{"time":143864,"text":"and we're going to look at the data through a visualization tool"},{"time":146940,"text":"that I've been working on in partnership with Autodesk."},{"time":150480,"text":"The way that you look at this data is,"},{"time":152952,"text":"first, look around the outside of the circle."},{"time":156530,"text":"You'll see broad bacterial groups,"},{"time":159552,"text":"and if you look at the shape of this pink lobe,"},{"time":162392,"text":"it tells you something about the relative abundance of each group."},{"time":165408,"text":"So at 12 o'clock, you'll see that offices have a lot of"},{"time":167904,"text":"alphaproteobacteria, and at one o'clock"},{"time":170465,"text":"you'll see that bacilli are relatively rare."}]},{"cues":[{"time":174660,"text":"Let's take a look at what's going on in different space types in this building."},{"time":179023,"text":"If you look inside the restrooms,"},{"time":181045,"text":"they all have really similar ecosystems,"},{"time":184175,"text":"and if you were to look inside the classrooms,"},{"time":186503,"text":"those also have similar ecosystems."},{"time":189369,"text":"But if you look across these space types,"},{"time":191783,"text":"you can see that they're fundamentally different"},{"time":194180,"text":"from one another."},{"time":196335,"text":"I like to think of bathrooms like a tropical rainforest."},{"time":199328,"text":"I told Tim, \"If you could just see the microbes,"},{"time":201815,"text":"it's kind of like being in Costa Rica. Kind of.\""},{"time":205854,"text":"And I also like to think of offices as being a temperate grassland."}]},{"cues":[{"time":210377,"text":"This perspective is a really powerful one for designers,"},{"time":214589,"text":"because you can bring on principles of ecology,"},{"time":218016,"text":"and a really important principle of ecology is dispersal,"},{"time":220928,"text":"the way organisms move around."},{"time":223655,"text":"We know that microbes are dispersed around by people"},{"time":227839,"text":"and by air."},{"time":228910,"text":"So the very first thing we wanted to do in this building"},{"time":231747,"text":"was look at the air system."},{"time":233600,"text":"Mechanical engineers design air handling units"},{"time":236832,"text":"to make sure that people are comfortable,"},{"time":239024,"text":"that the air flow and temperature is just right."},{"time":241577,"text":"They do this using principles of physics and chemistry,"},{"time":245121,"text":"but they could also be using biology."},{"time":249495,"text":"If you look at the microbes"},{"time":251607,"text":"in one of the air handling units in this building,"},{"time":254657,"text":"you'll see that they're all very similar to one another."},{"time":258648,"text":"And if you compare this to the microbes"},{"time":262183,"text":"in a different air handling unit,"},{"time":264327,"text":"you'll see that they're fundamentally different."},{"time":267039,"text":"The rooms in this building are like islands in an archipelago,"},{"time":270590,"text":"and what that means is that mechanical engineers"},{"time":273447,"text":"are like eco-engineers, and they have the ability"},{"time":276123,"text":"to structure biomes in this building the way that they want to."}]},{"cues":[{"time":281707,"text":"Another facet of how microbes get around is by people,"},{"time":285815,"text":"and designers often cluster rooms together"},{"time":288982,"text":"to facilitate interactions among people,"},{"time":291037,"text":"or the sharing of ideas, like in labs and in offices."},{"time":294509,"text":"Given that microbes travel around with people,"},{"time":297183,"text":"you might expect to see rooms that are close together"},{"time":299856,"text":"have really similar biomes."},{"time":302111,"text":"And that is exactly what we found."},{"time":304591,"text":"If you look at classrooms right adjacent to one another,"},{"time":307758,"text":"they have very similar ecosystems,"},{"time":309957,"text":"but if you go to an office"},{"time":313096,"text":"that is a farther walking distance away,"},{"time":316144,"text":"the ecosystem is fundamentally different."},{"time":318880,"text":"And when I see the power that dispersal has"},{"time":323425,"text":"on these biogeographic patterns,"},{"time":325705,"text":"it makes me think that it's possible"},{"time":328264,"text":"to tackle really challenging problems,"},{"time":332000,"text":"like hospital-acquired infections."},{"time":334461,"text":"I believe this has got to be, in part,"},{"time":337067,"text":"a building ecology problem."}]},{"cues":[{"time":340710,"text":"All right, I'm going to tell you one more story about this building."},{"time":344502,"text":"I am collaborating with Charlie Brown."},{"time":347967,"text":"He's an architect,"},{"time":349508,"text":"and Charlie is deeply concerned about global climate change."},{"time":354841,"text":"He's dedicated his life to sustainable design."},{"time":357785,"text":"When he met me and realized that it was possible for him"},{"time":360881,"text":"to study in a quantitative way"},{"time":363057,"text":"how his design choices impacted"},{"time":365633,"text":"the ecology and biology of this building,"},{"time":368593,"text":"he got really excited, because it added a new dimension to what he did."},{"time":373102,"text":"He went from thinking just about energy"},{"time":374970,"text":"to also starting to think about human health."},{"time":378458,"text":"He helped design some of the air handling systems"},{"time":382319,"text":"in this building and the way it was ventilated."}]},{"cues":[{"time":384513,"text":"So what I'm first going to show you is"},{"time":387235,"text":"air that we sampled outside of the building."},{"time":390794,"text":"What you're looking at is a signature of bacterial communities"},{"time":394961,"text":"in the outdoor air, and how they vary over time."},{"time":398937,"text":"Next I'm going to show you what happened"},{"time":401925,"text":"when we experimentally manipulated classrooms."},{"time":405574,"text":"We blocked them off at night"},{"time":407189,"text":"so that they got no ventilation."},{"time":409455,"text":"A lot of buildings are operated this way,"},{"time":411632,"text":"probably where you work,"},{"time":413383,"text":"and companies do this to save money on their energy bill."},{"time":416354,"text":"What we found is that these rooms remained relatively stagnant"},{"time":420281,"text":"until Saturday, when we opened the vents up again."},{"time":423340,"text":"When you walked into those rooms,"},{"time":424922,"text":"they smelled really bad,"},{"time":426897,"text":"and our data suggests that it had something to do with"},{"time":429999,"text":"leaving behind the airborne bacterial soup"},{"time":433066,"text":"from people the day before."},{"time":435745,"text":"Contrast this to rooms"},{"time":437917,"text":"that were designed using a sustainable passive design strategy"},{"time":442198,"text":"where air came in from the outside through louvers."},{"time":445978,"text":"In these rooms, the air tracked the outdoor air relatively well,"},{"time":450775,"text":"and when Charlie saw this, he got really excited."},{"time":452910,"text":"He felt like he had made a good choice"},{"time":455021,"text":"with the design process"},{"time":456755,"text":"because it was both energy efficient"},{"time":459150,"text":"and it washed away the building's resident microbial landscape."}]},{"cues":[{"time":464439,"text":"The examples that I just gave you are about architecture,"},{"time":467481,"text":"but they're relevant to the design of anything."},{"time":469994,"text":"Imagine designing with the kinds of microbes that we want"},{"time":474164,"text":"in a plane"},{"time":475582,"text":"or on a phone."}]},{"cues":[{"time":478515,"text":"There's a new microbe, I just discovered it."},{"time":480969,"text":"It's called BLIS, and it's been shown"},{"time":483849,"text":"to both ward off pathogens"},{"time":486033,"text":"and give you good breath."},{"time":488178,"text":"Wouldn't it be awesome if we all had BLIS on our phones?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":494197,"text":"A conscious approach to design,"},{"time":496567,"text":"I'm calling it bioinformed design,"},{"time":499448,"text":"and I think it's possible."}]},{"cues":[{"time":500934,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":502372,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}